Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That was pathetic! Are you through?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.17,0:02:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those of you who can't put up with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this level of field drill, go home now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.17,0:02:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is not the SDF! This is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Space Panzer Grenadiers... SPG!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Restart the drill!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Mankind continually runs{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}down this road called life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:03:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Occasionally, a person has to{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}choose which road they should take.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Choices"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.82,0:03:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Undergo training?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.82,0:03:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You mean... me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.15,0:03:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so the units can\N{\c&He1e1e1&}understand each other better,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.86,0:03:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and strengthen their relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.16,0:03:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's what the company line is, anyhow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.90,0:03:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The real purpose is to retrain\N{\c&He1e1e1&}new recruits. Brace yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.83,0:03:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Schnader, from my unit, and Ai\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Spica Platoon are also being sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}so you can all go through\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the wringer together...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...with the most elite force\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the Space Panzer Grenadiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The SPG...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The outfit my brother was in, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:03:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's one more important matter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I called you here to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.46,0:04:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Important matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} is being poached?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The information is reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.21,0:04:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is still just between us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but if they acknowledge him\N{\c&He1e1e1&}during this upcoming training,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.31,0:04:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}they say he'll be bumped up to the SPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.22,0:04:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right now, Yuuki is probably getting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}word of this from Captain Murase.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.22,0:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}From Captain Murase?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come to think of it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Johansson of the SPG
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}was one of Captain Murase's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}upperclassmen in training school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.56,0:04:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It sounds like they're serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.90,0:04:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They say that {\i1}Yuuki-san{\i0} has drawn\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the SPG's attention for some time, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.57,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Isn't that amazing? To join\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the SPG because {\i1}they{\i0} want you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} isn't leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.58,0:05:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- I mean, isn't strange, seeing as\N{\c&He1e1e1&}how my grades were higher than his?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's no way our reckless, stubborn,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}obtuse {\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} could join the SPG!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.39,0:05:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's up to him to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.20,0:05:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's the one who can make\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the decisions about his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.53,0:05:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.21,0:05:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.55,0:05:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, I heard from Murase\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that they're talking about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's no rush. You can always give them\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your answer during the training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a big deal for you. For us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.57,0:05:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But I want you to keep this in mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.24,0:06:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The desire to protect the peace\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and security of others will be the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.31,0:06:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}no matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.18,0:06:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sure Captain Yuuki must\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.52,0:06:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.88,0:06:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.90,0:06:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Enemy craft approaching\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the left at 8 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Escape track is as indicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.51,0:07:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Enemy craft also approaching\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are four of them... no, six!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.85,0:07:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please hold on,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}our escape track will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.51,0:07:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are even more enemy craft now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.18,0:07:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We can't go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.21,0:07:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Were you planning to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}catch up to it on foot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's time you were in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.20,0:08:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sleeping is also part of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your duties. Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}R- right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I heard from Captain Murase\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about the SPG and me... and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it because I am\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the son of Yuuki Wataru,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:09:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the brother of Yuuki Mamoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've even got the exact\N{\c&He1e1e1&}same determination that he had.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He also gritted his teeth\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and endured through my training.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Someone with as much nerve as he had...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd never seen anyone\N{\c&He1e1e1&}like Yuuki Mamoru before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I still think about him now, sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.85,0:09:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What if he were still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why did you join the SDF? Was it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just out of the awe of it all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's what it was at first.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}But now, it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I want to protect everyone's happiness.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanting to maintain people's security,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and defend peace will be the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}no matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.21,0:10:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whether you're in the SDF, or in the SPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What the SPG needs right now\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is the strength of youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The ardent zeal of the young.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Like Yuuki Mamoru had...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and like you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're waiting for you, Yuuki Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For crying out loud...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this platoon sure is rough on us, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.33,0:10:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't even get one date in like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.27,0:10:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have to find someone first.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Then you can complain about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Listen, one trip into the city, and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.60,0:10:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.61,0:11:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hi, hi! Such hard workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yo, Old Lady Kinuko! I'll take my usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.55,0:11:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.55,0:11:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And, for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.55,0:11:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so sweet! Too sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is just the thing after work.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Huh, Manabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.57,0:11:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.57,0:11:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All we've lost is {\i1}Manabu-chan,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and yet it seems so empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then, let's bet on\N{\c&He1e1e1&}whether he comes back or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll bet 500 ables that he comes back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.92,0:11:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then, so will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, you know it, huh, Old Lady Kinuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, which way are you betting?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.93,0:11:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In that case, I'll bet\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that he joins the SPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay. I'm sure he will come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-san{\i0} is a member of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon. He is our friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If going over to the SPG is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what is best for {\i1}Yuuki-kun,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}then we can't say that sort of thing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and make him second-guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have to send him off with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.23,0:12:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Louis-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.58,0:12:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I tell you, practical training\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in a magnetic storm like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the SPG are really sticking it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once this is over, our training is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.92,0:12:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's do our best, {\i1}Yuuki-san.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the lifeboat.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We have arrived on {\i1}No. 650.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.87,0:13:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're now going to rescue\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the passengers and lead them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}666,{\i0} copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}After speedily rescuing the passengers,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}please restart {\i1}No. 650's{\i0} engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and get out of the magnetic storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please stay calm, and keep\N{\c&He1e1e1&}moving without panicking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.55,0:13:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.55,0:13:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please follow our instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanting to maintain people's security,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and defend peace will be the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.09,0:13:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}no matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.89,0:13:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whether you're in the SDF, or in the SPG.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'll worry about it after the drill.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.24,0:13:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.58,0:13:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please move quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.58,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come, this way! Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everything will be all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.92,0:14:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}These guys are pretty good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's the last of the passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger. I'll get the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}dinghy ready to launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.87,0:14:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All we have to do now\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is restart the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.53,0:14:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. I'll go do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.87,0:14:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Detecting an anomaly\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in the magnetic storm!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.08,0:14:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The energy is climbing at a sharp rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you okay!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-san{\i0} is still aboard {\i1}No. 650!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Crewman Yuuki, come in! Crewman Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Communication lines are down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our sensors are all blacked out!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We can't ascertain the status of {\i1}No. 650!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.53,0:15:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}666{\i0} is going to move in now\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to rescue {\i1}No. 650.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.54,0:15:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Main engine has been damaged!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Output has dropped by 30%!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.54,0:15:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Switch to the auxiliary engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.21,0:15:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No. 650{\i0} is lost!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We've lost sight of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Widen the search area to G Area!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.72,0:15:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't overlook any readings,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}no matter how small!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.56,0:15:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do your best, whatever the situation!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That is our duty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Adrift in the storm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Yuuki. {\i1}666,{\i0} please come in!\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}666,{\i0} please come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}What should I do? What should I?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's like I always tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.53,0:16:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Keep calm. Then you'll be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}able to use correct judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The song of the engine.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The engine is still running!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.89,0:16:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hang in there, {\i1}Yuuki-san.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:17:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's bet on it, Manabu.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}500 ables says it will turn out fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How about it? Are you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.19,0:17:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Is this hopeless?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.19,0:17:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Steady on, {\i1}Yuuki-kun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.20,0:17:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.55,0:17:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Six hours have passed since the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We still cannot be sure\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of {\i1}No. 650's{\i0} location.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.16,0:18:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've got to be kidding me!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}He's definitely alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.50,0:18:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He's Yuuki Manabu, of the SDF!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.18,0:18:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.19,0:18:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.53,0:18:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.87,0:18:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mission... accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.16,0:19:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki did great! He got out of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that situation all by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I hate to admit it, but he's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a shoe-in for the SPG now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.83,0:19:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You win the bet, Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.51,0:19:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone, smile! Smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have to send him off with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For crying out loud,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what is he thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki. Yuuki Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He turned down joining the SPG!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Would you tell me what your reasons are?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I still want to learn\N{\c&He1e1e1&}some more with Sirius Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.89,0:20:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Besides?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}My desire to maintain people's security,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and defend peace will be the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.09,0:20:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}no matter where I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whether I'm in the SPG,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or in the SDF.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.57,0:20:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That rascal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.57,0:20:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How could he say such a grown-up thing!?\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'm{\i0} the one who had the better grades!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.91,0:20:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Louis-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.92,0:20:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} really had everyone worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not going to be satisfied...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}until he is really taken to task...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, you're right. He leaves for just\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a little while, and gets all cocky on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If we're going to rail on him,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that's my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please go easy on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, you can count on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.94,0:20:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People continue to run along.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.27,0:21:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Even when they don't know{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}what waits for them ahead,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.04,0:21:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}people continue to run along.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Together with their friends,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and with faith in their futures.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.56,0:21:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.25,0:21:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}How many nights have{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.26,0:22:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Constantly having dreams of the hope{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.94,0:22:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The smiles and tears{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.95,0:22:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}come to mind every time{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.29,0:22:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and I set forth again toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.96,0:22:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The joyful light of the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.58,0:22:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No matter how far apart we are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.25,0:23:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}My heart wishes always{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to be at your side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.87,0:23:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Next Time"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.77,0:23:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}A distress signal from Planet Coulomb.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.11,0:23:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}What we came across in{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that melancholy city was...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Next time on Tales of the{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Galaxy Railways, Episode 21:{\i0} "Rebellion"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.78,0:23:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}We're going to encounter{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}something at the next station.{\i0}